	   <tr><td colspan=2>On soloing:<br><br>Your pet wouldn't last long enough to make it worth while using it as you described.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our pets are about doing damage, they can't stand up to direct mobs attacks for long.  The lvl 49 pet is a big improvment but even then you will need to buff it with speed and regen.  It is far better to let the mob beat on you while the pet attacks it.  <br><br>Concerning Melee:<br>I melee all the time, lvl 50 atm.  90% of the time i eather solo or am part of a small group.  My 2hb skill is maxed at 200 and I often hit for over 100 hps of damage.  A ranger friend (lvl 49) and I can pull giants nonstop in BW.  I jsut keep everyone buffed, and cast slow. I  have seen other healer/tank, combos hunting the giants and they kill slower, and have more down time, when the shaman doesn't help melee.  Can we melee as good as the pure tanks? NO.  Should we melee in large groups? Not after lvl 19 or so.  Sould we melee on raids? No.  <br>At high lvl and in large groups shaman are buffers/debuffers (slow is a debuff) and back up healers.  Soloing, at low levels, and in small groups shaman are melee casters.   <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
