	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi there...all the shaman newbies gonna let ya in on a few things.The bashing,and direct damage wont last forever.Once you Ding about Lvl 19,and you are still meleeing,you will be kicked outta group most likely.Lvl 19-39 can be a healer if needed really.Shaman tend to&nbsp;&nbsp;have trouble healing after Lvl 35.Sows and buffs are our thing...oh and the most important thing,Slow.Lvl 30 you should start slowing mobs,So important.Rarely will you heal and your heals will start to seem useless to tanks.Lvl 51+ it is all about slowing and buffing,that's all you will do in a group unless you are in a easy camp that you can keep up with heals.You get a very nice slow(best out there)that slows mob of about 60percent to 75percent of health.So helpful in dungeons in other places where the mobs hit hard,fast,and have a crap load of HP.Ac and wisdom are important at this level.I suggest you try and average the two out a little.Catch as little aggro as possible(Example:Dont immediately slow Mob before tanks can get a taunt or two in,and a big one DO NOT SIT IMMEDIATELY AFTER...or you will get slaughtered especially with low AC.You will be lucky to last a few seconds especially when you are the one trying to slow 3-4 mobs in one fight.You sit down and they all turn directly to you.Give it some time.I usually do a 5,4,3,2,1,sit count on a single mob.Might want to wait a little longer for tanks to catch aggro when you are fighting numeros mobs.)Most I say here is Group stuff soloing is a whole different thing.Many shamans do a little of both but it also depends on the person.I personally group most the time as you can see from the information but soloing is ok too.Usually when soloing,I still slow the mob.It can and will save your life...guranteed.So you have 30 seconds more down time...booohooo,oh well.Better than at Lvl 51 losing 4 hours of work cause you can't a rez.Next you might want to root,dot,(try for a second dot if root did not break on first dot),then root again.Sit back,relax and watch the bastage die a painful death.A few DD's at the end helps if you do not want to waste the mana on another dot or two,but woudlnt recommend in beginning or middle of fight due to it breaks root.Let dots do as much work as possible.If you run outta mana and its still got a little left,melee it.That is another thing we are known for hehe.If it is already slowed you will most likely have it on the run in no time with a few scratches and bruises.Or just save that little bit of mana for root if you know you do not have enough to finish it,and meditate while he is sitting there waiting to attack,then hit him with a dot or DD to kill him.Sorry for the incredibly long post but this is much of what I have learned and should serve you well,whether you group or solo = )<br><br><br>Lvl 52 Barbarian Mystic<br>Bertoxxulous<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
