	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The below is probably as succinct as it gets:<br><br>From eq.castersrealm.com<br><br>Religion<br><br>Since Shaman are generally hated because they are evil it doesn't matter a great deal what religion you choose.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you are evil, you can eventually avoid being kill on Sight in many zones, but you will never be able to trade there because of your race.  It is more fun to pick a religion, and maybe you will find a religion-only item at some point that will make it useful.  There is no real advantage to be gained from being Agnostic as a Shaman.<br><br>***<br><br>One thing that it doesn't cover is if you're Barbarian, you aren't really <i>evil</i>, but you aren't going to be loved and adored, either. Being Barbarian, however, imposes the least starting penalty faction-wise. Chosing Tribunal over agnostic gets you at least one quest in Halas. Up to you whether that one quest is worth additional faction hits everywhere else. (I don't think being Tribunal makes you KoS anywhere that you wouldn't otherwise be, but you may find prices higher and/or vendors more snooty.)<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
