	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have a question for everyone that plays in Seb. I was in a group the other day when after an hour and a half (aprox)Had looted a total of about 4 times with a group that was a fast pulling group. I got lucky enough to loot 3 gems (Not Rare), when the cleric asked for 1 of them durring this time. I figure sure not a prob because of the Symbol that she cast. But after an hour and a half I had 2 of the 3 that I had looted. When she demanded that I give her the other 2 as well. I said to heck with the group announced that after the pull I would just gate out. And did so (with the 2 remaining gems with chr buff didn't net but 80p).<br><br>My question is, is it wrong for me to expect to get somthing out of a group? We didn't have any named pop. I believe a cleric should get to cover expenses but should they get all the reg gems that drop. Not just enough to cover expenses plus a fair share.<br><br>She in turn called me a loot hog and ninja looter when thats all I had looted in aprox an hour and a half (4 times) got lucky and looted I think it was 3 fire opals or what ever it is. She got 1 leaving me 2. That means she got 40p worth from me and if everyone else gave her there reg gems she could have made a bundle. Her logic is I should pay for all her symbles she uses on raids. When I'm not in her guild.<br><br>To me I can see giving her 2 out of 6 stones. And the raid she's on should pay for her symble not reglar exp groups.<br><br>Does this sound unreasonalble of me?<br><br>Thanks sorry it's such a long post.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
